text: Pleasant tasting sourdough pizza. Generous topping. Would prefer if the crust is crispier. Tomato base on pizza is sweet instead of sour. Can see the real cherry tomatos in the sauce, so not those puréed type. Order at the cashier of Baker and Cook.
Plank has many branches across the island, and I've yet to find a branch that wasn't satisfactory. Get the pizzas, the pastas are good but not mind-blowing.

Sourdough chicken BBQ pulled pizza was not up-to my expectations. Chicken smells funny, maybe it’s a frozen chicken, pizza base is ok I guess. The Bolognese pasta too sour for my liking lacking of umami taste. The only good thing was fries, chicken tender and beer.  Need improvement.
Well made pizza with chewy sourdough base. A tiny but burnt on the bottom part but overall pretty good. On the more expensive price range for a pizza.

Loved the tzatziki so much we had to ask for more.
The pepperoni pizza was good but on the slightly pricier side. Overall satisfied with the meal and service
